# WorldBase workflow

Read [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md) at session start. Use [`LLM_HANDOFF.md`](../../LLM_HANDOFF.md) for endpoint lists and troubleshooting.

## Before coding

1. Confirm backend: `GET /api/health/ping` (or note if stack is down).
2. For briefing work: skim `GET /api/briefing` or run `python -m unittest test_operator_briefing` in `backend/`.
3. After substantive changes: `.\scripts\smoke-test.ps1` when feasible.

## Default focus

Briefing digest, operator region (Thailand), GDELT local, Pi `/api/node/pull`, FULL SITUATION / SITUATIONS UX.

## Out of scope unless asked

HAK_GAL firewall (`firewall_bridge.py`, `:8001`, FIREWALL tab, chat 🛡️ toggle). Do not implement “hide firewall in UI” when the user means **work focus** — ask if unclear.

## Guardrails

- UI strings English (`.cursor/rules/english-only.mdc`); `WORLDBASE_BRIEFING_LANG=de` only affects briefing text.
- PowerShell paths with spaces: `-LiteralPath`.
- No git commits unless the user explicitly requests them.
- Minimal, focused diffs — reuse existing bridges and HUD patterns.
